### Redis Stream Operations
### Add event to user activity stream
POST {{BaseUrl}}/streams/user:123:activity/add
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fields": {
    "action": "login",
    "timestamp": "2024-01-15T10:30:00Z",
    "ip": "192.168.1.100",
    "device": "mobile"
  }
}

### Add another event to the stream
POST {{BaseUrl}}/streams/user:123:activity/add
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fields": {
    "action": "view_product",
    "timestamp": "2024-01-15T10:35:00Z",
    "product_id": "123",
    "category": "electronics"
  }
}

### Add purchase event
POST {{BaseUrl}}/streams/user:123:activity/add
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fields": {
    "action": "purchase",
    "timestamp": "2024-01-15T10:45:00Z",
    "product_id": "123",
    "amount": "99.99",
    "currency": "USD"
  }
}

### Read all events from the stream
GET {{BaseUrl}}/streams/user:123:activity?startId=0&count=10

### Read recent events (limit to 5)
GET {{BaseUrl}}/streams/user:123:activity?startId=0&count=5

### Add sensor data stream
POST {{BaseUrl}}/streams/sensor:temperature/add
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fields": {
    "sensor_id": "temp_001",
    "temperature": "23.5",
    "humidity": "65.2",
    "location": "server_room"
  }
}

### Add another sensor reading
POST {{BaseUrl}}/streams/sensor:temperature/add
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fields": {
    "sensor_id": "temp_001",
    "temperature": "24.1",
    "humidity": "64.8",
    "location": "server_room"
  }
}

### Read sensor data
GET {{BaseUrl}}/streams/sensor:temperature?startId=0&count=10

### Add log entry stream
POST {{BaseUrl}}/streams/app:logs/add
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fields": {
    "level": "INFO",
    "message": "User authenticated successfully",
    "user_id": "123",
    "service": "auth-service"
  }
}

### Add error log
POST {{BaseUrl}}/streams/app:logs/add
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fields": {
    "level": "ERROR",
    "message": "Database connection failed",
    "error_code": "DB_001",
    "service": "user-service"
  }
}

### Read application logs
GET {{BaseUrl}}/streams/app:logs?startId=0&count=20
